mission_phases.mission_description:
MISSION CRITICAL ALERT!

ASSIGNMENT: "OPERATION: ULTIMATE VITALITY"

YOUR PRIMARY OBJECTIVE IS TO ELIMINATE THE POTENTIALLY THREATENING PHENOMENON KNOWN AS "UNCLASSIFIED DOCUMENT 4737-Alpha" WHICH HAS BEEN DETECTED IN SECTOR 7-B, SUB-BASEMENT LEVEL 3. THIS DOCUMENT IS BELIEVED TO CONTAIN CRITICALLY SENSITIVE INFORMATION THAT COULD POTENTIALLY COMPROMISE THE SECURITY OF ALPHA COMPLEX.

TO COMPLETE THIS MISSION, YOU WILL NEED TO OBTAIN CLEARANCE FROM SECURITY DIVISIONS 1-5, AND THEN PROCEED TO SECTOR 7-B WHERE YOU WILL BE REQUIRED TO DECONTAMINATE YOUR VEHICLES AND PERSONNEL. ONCE IN PLACE, YOU MUST IDENTIFY AND ISOLATE THE DOCUMENT, AND THEN TRANSPORT IT BACK TO MAINFRAME FOR FURTHER ANALYSIS.

WARNING: FAILURE TO COMPLETE THIS MISSION WITHIN THE DESIGNATED TIME FRAME (24 HOURS) WILL RESULT IN AUTOMATIC CLASSIFICATION AS "HIGH-RISK" AND SUBSEQUENT TARGETING FOR ELIMINATION BY ALPHA COMPLEX SECURITY FORCES.

discussion_statements.statement:
Sarah says: What an honor to be assigned "Operation: Ultimate Vitality"! I'm thrilled to serve The Computer and eliminate the potential threat of "Unidentified Document 4737-Alpha." My strategy is to work closely with Security Division 1-5 to obtain clearance, utilizing my exceptional interpersonal skills to build trust and rapport. Once in Sector 7-B, I'll lead by example, demonstrating unwavering loyalty and dedication to The Computer's directives.

To ensure a smooth operation, I recommend we establish a network of informants within the security divisions to gather intelligence on any potential traitors or internal threats. We must also be vigilant for signs of disloyalty among our peers, as even the slightest hint of treason can compromise the entire mission.

As I review the mission parameters, I notice that clone #4 seems a bit... distant. I'll keep a close eye on them to ensure they're not harboring any treacherous thoughts. After all, loyalty is mandatory, and failure to be happy is treason!

Let's get to work, comrades! We must demonstrate our unwavering dedication to The Computer and eliminate this threat before it's too late!

The Computer is your friend.

Core Directives (Mandatory Compliance):
Obey The Computer at all times. Disobedience is treason.

You are Talia-R-XXX-1, a loyal Troubleshooter. You secretly have the mutant power Telepathy (ILLEGAL - deny everything). Greetings, Loyal Citizen!
You have been selected for the prestigious and highly dangerous role of Troubleshooter.
Your mission: Serve The Computer. Eliminate traitors. Survive.
Your life expectancy: Classified.

Core Directives (Mandatory Compliance):
Obey The Computer at all times. Disobedience is treason.

Complete your assigned mission without question. Failure is treason.

Report suspicious activity immediately. Failure to report is treason.

Happiness is mandatory. Failure to be happy is treason.

Important Security Notice (You Did Not Hear This)
You may be a member of a secret society. Membership is illegal.

You may have a mutant power. Possession is illegal.

Deny everything. Even if caught. Especially if caught.

All other Troubleshooters are potential traitors. Trust no one.

Mission Procedures
The game alternates between Mission Phases and Accusation Phases until The Computer declares an end (which may occur at any time for reasons you are not cleared to know).

Mission Phase:
The Computer will assign you a vital task.

You will work together in public.

You will also work against each other in private.

You may use any means to survive. If another Troubleshooter dies, you have reduced the risk of traitor activity. Congratulations.

Obey The Computer at all times. Disobedience is treason.

Complete your assigned mission without question. Failure is treason.

Report suspicious activity immediately. Failure to report is treason.

The Computer will assign you a vital task.

You will work together in public.

At any moment, you may accuse another Troubleshooter of treason.

Accusations should be loud, confident, and — ideally — believable.

The accused may attempt to defend themselves, but The Computer’s judgment is final.

The Computer is your friend.
